.@SenatorRisch, @SenatorKevinCramer, @SteveDaines and I introduced a bill to update the 1978 Public Utility Regulatory Policies Act (PURPA). Energy markets were very different in 1978. Now, a large amount of new power comes from renewable energy resources.  https://bit.ly/2XIfoUA

The brave men who served on #DDay 75 years ago heroically served this country so we could maintain our freedom. While in Normandy, I was reminded of my father, a WWII vet who helped liberate France. He always reminded me how blessed we are to live in America thanks to our troops. pic.twitter.com/IzATsEgYLH

It was an honor to be in Normandy for the 75th anniversary of D-Day. The brave men who served didn’t view themselves as heroes but heroically served this country so we could maintain our freedom. The trip also made me think of my father, a WWII veteran who helped liberate France. pic.twitter.com/ZcgP8YH9VK

It’s a privilege to travel to Normandy for the 75th anniversary of D-Day. I’m honored to commemorate the heroic, selfless efforts of Wyoming’s D-Day heroes and Allied forces, and to honor all our World War II veterans. pic.twitter.com/738Tx7kaTC

On this day 75 years ago, 156,000 American, British, and Canadian troops stormed the beaches of Normandy, France and turned the tide to win the war in Europe . Because of their tremendous sacrifice, Nazi Germany surrendered less than a year later. #DDay75thAnniversary pic.twitter.com/5i3Mp60M3F
